Understanding if there is any relationship between RND and Profit¶

In [7]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
In [8]:
sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='RND', y='PROFIT')
Out[8]:
<Axes: xlabel='RND', ylabel='PROFIT'>
In [9]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='RND', y='PROFIT')
plt.title('Scatterplot for RND vs PROFIT')
plt.grid()
plt.show()

RND and PROFIT are almost linearly dependent on each other¶

RND increases, profit also increases

In [10]:
